Unibep on the border | EurobuildCEE Mariola Bitner on the implementation of ESG policies (Eurobuild FM) Jonathan Cohen on the photovoltaic revolution [Eurobuild FM] Béranger Dumont on recent acquisitions and the market's prospects (Eurobuild FM) April 2, World Autism Awareness Day Tax revolution for real estate Light it up Blue Robert Dobrzycki's Outstanding Contribution to the Real Estate Market The many advantages of forward funding The 7th Invested Interest Investment Market Conference The Eurobuild Awards Gala 2021 The 5th Suits on bikes The 20th Eurobuild CEE Golf Tournament The 16th Annual Eurobuild CEE Tennis Tournament The 7th Invested Interest Investment Market Conference The 19th Eurobuild CEE Golf Tournament Infrastructure Advertisement schedule 04 April 2018 Eurobuild CEE POLAND Unibep has been chosen by the State Fiscal Service of Ukraine to be the general contractor to build a border crossing in Shehyni (near Medyka) on the Ukrainian-Polish border. 
The contract is worth EUR 15.6 mln net (app. PLN 66 mln), which is to be financed by a loan from the Polish to the Ukrainian government, while payments for the execution of the contract will be made directly to Unibep through Bank Gospodarstwa Krajowego. 
The contract covers the design and execution of the construction and installation work for the border crossing. 
The completion of the work has been scheduled for Q3 2020. 
